            . I am a toll collector at Newgate market. On the 11th of August, a little before eight o'clock in the forenoon. I was in the market and saw the prisoner take a handkerchief out of Mr. Edward's left hand pocket; I collared him with it in his hand; he said it was not worth two pence.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-130-person1111">
